тнР What is Candidate Key? (English Explanation)

A candidate key is a minimal set of attributes that can uniquely identify a row.
ЁЯСЙ тАЬCandidateтАЭ means candidate to become Primary Key.

тЮб It must be unique
тЮб Cannot be NULL
тЮб No extra/unnecessary column allowed
тЮб From these, one is chosen as Primary Key

